<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="14.[108,1213,337,1335]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
ETYMOLOGY: The specific epithet is from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[748,818,1271,1296]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">penna</emphasis>
(wing, feather) and 
<emphasis box="[1052,1119,1271,1297]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">brevis</emphasis>
(short), referring to the shortened wing that characterizes this species.
</paragraph>
